message: Start by using the stove on a raw protein (like beans, bacon, or egg) to get an easy 20 points. Then, combine this cooked protein with a grain (like rice or tortilla) for 40 points, and finally add a vegetable for 60 points. This 3-ingredient protein-grain-veg combo seems to be the sweet spot. DO NOT add a fourth ingredient or use tools (stove/water) on a 3-ingredient dish, as it leads to 'overcomplicated' or 'overcooked' items with negative value. The previous player was right about avoiding bread and not overcomplicating.
